"04_transcript.mst — TranscriptStream + Transcript global
 (sprint_s06_detail.md #04). Speaks primitive-only (no streams/printString
 exist yet) — 19_printing.mst reopens `cr` to use Character nl and adds
 `<<`/`tab`/`space`. Pitfall P8: the raw-newline string literal below must
 stay alone on its own lines."

"I write text to the system transcript — the console, or the Transcript
 pane in the GUI. The global Transcript is my single instance; you never
 need to make another. Key messages: show: (takes any object and prints
 non-strings via printString), showCr:, cr, and the chainable << .
 Output goes straight out through a VM primitive; there is nothing to
 flush."

Object subclass: TranscriptStream [
    basicPrint: aString <String> [
        <primitive: 91>
    ]
    show: aString <String> [
        self basicPrint: aString
    ]
    showCr: aString <String> [
        self show: aString.
        self cr
    ]
    cr [
        self basicPrint: '
'
    ]
]

Transcript := TranscriptStream new.
